msContents.summary: A transcription of records concerning the offices of chancellor and minister of justice (garde des sceaux) in chronological order, from the 13th century to ca. 1633. A table of contents detailing each record precedes the records.
msContents.textLang: Middle French, with a few early records in Latin

msItem.title: Lettres, memoires, titres, et actes concernans les chanceliers et gardes des seaux sic de France, leur origine, erections, droits, et honneurs appartenans aux dites charges
Table of contents, f. ii recto

supportDesc.extent: 368 leaves : 299 x 182 (220 x 105) mm. bound to 307 x 220 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, v (contemporary paper) + 368 + iv (contemporary paper); [xvi], 1-352; contemporary foliation in ink, upper right recto.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 22 long lines; frame-ruled in drypoint.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by a single hand.

binding.p: Contemporary calf with the arms of the Feydeau de Brou family.

history.provenance: Bound for François or Denis I. (fl. 1620-1640) Feydeau de Brou, both affiliated with the Parlement de Paris.
A letter from L. Farjas laid in the book indicates that he gave it as a gift to an unknown recipient.
